# Self-Optimizing Agentic Interface (SOAI) Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
The purpose of this plan is to outline the architecture, necessary libraries, folder structure, and class-based design for the Self-Optimizing Agentic Interface (SOAI). The goal is to build an application that utilizes user interactions (sensors) to probabilistically calculate user intent and re-render the UI structure dynamically using "Superposition" (React, Framer Motion, and Jotai).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please review this implementation plan. Specifically, confirm if the class-based separation of concerns in the `lib/services/` directory aligns with your vision. Once approved, I can proceed with the execution phase based on this plan.

## Proposed Technologies & Libraries
To achieve a high-performance Agentic Generative UI, we will rely on the following tech stack:

- **Framework:** Next.js 16 (App Router) — For React Server Components, Partial Prerendering, and Edge API Routes.
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (`tailwindcss`, `tailwind-merge`, `clsx`) — For high-speed utility class styling and dynamic UI manipulation.
- **Animations:** Framer Motion (`framer-motion`) — Essential for "Superposition" morphing using `layoutId`.
- **State Management:** Jotai (`jotai`) — For high-frequency, atomic state updates (e.g., tracking the 0.0 - 1.0 probability vector).
- **AI Integration:** Vercel AI SDK (`ai`, `@ai-sdk/google`) — For orchestration and Generative UI tool calling with Gemini 2.5 Flash.
- **Database:** Supabase Client (`@supabase/supabase-js`) — For long-term user DNA persistence.
- **UI Components:** Shadcn/UI (Radix UI primitives, `lucide-react`) — For standard atomic "Lego" blocks.

## Folder Structure & Modularization

The codebase will be modularized to separate React view components from the core logical engine. The core logic will rely heavily on classes to maintain state and provide clean interfaces.

```text
soai/
├── app/                              # Next.js App Router
│   ├── api/
│   │   └── agent/
│   │       └── route.ts              # Edge API route for Vercel AI SDK
│   ├── globals.css                   # Global styles & Tailwind
│   ├── layout.tsx                    # Root layout containing providers
│   └── page.tsx                      # Main entry point with Superposition views
├── components/                       # React Components
│   ├── agentic/                      # Core SOAI visual components
│   │   └── SuperpositionContainer.tsx # Orchestrates the predictive shadow DOM
│   ├── sections/                     # Specific page sections
│   │   └── hero/                     # Hero View Variations
│   │       ├── HeroData.tsx          # Analytical persona view
│   │       ├── HeroStory.tsx         # Storyteller persona view
│   │       └── HeroDirect.tsx        # Transactional persona view
│   └── ui/                           # Shadcn/UI atomic elements
│       ├── button.tsx
│       └── card.tsx
├── hooks/                            # Custom React Hooks
│   ├── useBehavioralSensor.ts        # Bridges SensorService to React lifecycles
│   └── useIntent.ts                  # Bridges intentStore (Jotai) to components
├── lib/
│   ├── services/                     # 🧠 Class-based Core Logic
│   │   ├── AIService.ts              # Class to handle Vercel AI SDK interactions
│   │   ├── DatabaseService.ts        # Class to interact with Supabase vector store
│   │   └── SensorService.ts          # Class to compute velocity, hover intent, & pathing
│   ├── store/                        # Jotai State
│   │   └── intentStore.ts            # Atomic definitions for probability, velocity, persona
│   └── utils.ts                      # Tailwind and general utility functions
└── types/                            # TypeScript Definitions
    └── index.ts                      # Interfaces for Persona Vectors, Sensor Data, etc.
```

## Detailed Component Plans

### 1. `lib/services/SensorService.ts`
A class responsible for the math and physics behind user interaction.
- **Responsibilities:** Takes raw coordinates (`clientX`, `clientY`) and timestamps, returning computed velocity and trajectory vectors.
- **Why a Class?:** Better encapsulation of the mathematical formulas and recent positional history without clogging React components.

### 2. `lib/services/AIService.ts`
A class interfacing with the LLM.
- **Responsibilities:** Takes the calculated intent vectors and prepares context prompts for Vercel AI SDK to stream UI variations or personalize content text.

### 3. `components/agentic/SuperpositionContainer.tsx`
The intelligent container that wraps around variation components.
- Uses `AnimatePresence` and `motion.div` from Framer Motion.
- Uses `layoutId` to morph between the `HeroStory` and `HeroData` states without jarring visual jumps.
- Mounts non-active states with `opacity-0` and `pointer-events-none` for predictive Shadow DOM caching.

## Verification Plan
1. **Manual Verification**: Run the development server and verify standard layout loading.
2. **Sensor Testing**: Simulate various mouse velocities and read the logs of the `SensorService` to verify correct persona assignments (e.g. erratic fast movement -> Analytical, slow scrolling -> Storyteller).
3. **Superposition Testing**: Check if Framer Motion correctly morphs between variations with zero-latency visual swaps.
